    <briefdescription>
<para>class to create a fast xorshift-based pseudo-random number generator </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>unsigned integral type used as the internal state (supported uint32_t and uint64_t)</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
This class implements a lightweight xorshift pseudo-random number generator suitable for performance-critical paths such as schedulers, work-stealing victim selection, and randomized backoff. The implementation is branchless on the hot path and has a very small state footprint (one machine word). All operations are integer-only.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="attention"><para>The internal state must be seeded with a non-zero value. This class is not thread-safe. Each thread should maintain its own instance. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
